25|$|The Kazakh <b>Mobile</b> <b>forces</b> {{were created}} on 6 July 2000. On 11 August, the brigade was subordinated to the Southern Military District. The brigade {{became part of}} the <b>mobile</b> <b>forces</b> on 1 February 2001. The <b>mobile</b> <b>forces</b> were renamed the Airmobile Troops on 12 November 2003. With the growth of the Kazakh economy and {{increased}} funding, a partial reformation of the disbanded units began. The mortar batteries, the reconnaissance company, a heavy machine gun company armed with the NSV-12.7 and a reactive artillery battery equipped with the BM-21 Grad were formed. Brigade units tested new parachute systems and powered paragliding. Currently, there are around 1,000 soldiers in the brigade.|$|R
